Peel and finely dice @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and finely diced) and @onion{1/2}(finely diced) and finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(finely chopped). Boil @water{300%ml} in a #pot{} with half the @chicken stock pot{1/2}. Remove the core from the @green pepper{1}, cut into 1cm strips then cut it into small cubes. Finally, cut the @British chicken thighs{3} into bite-sized pieces.

Heat @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #non-stick pan{} on high heat. Cook chicken with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} until browned off on all sides. Now grate over @orange zest{1/4%tsp} and pour on @honey{2%tsp}. Toss for about ~{1%minute} before removing from the pan and keeping to the side.

Turn heat to medium and add @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Add the onion and cook off for a few mins. Add the @diced chorizo{1/4} to the pan with the garlic and green pepper. Cook for about ~{5%minutes}.

Add the chicken back into the pan with the juice of a quarter of your @orange{1}. Add in a few shakes of @Tabasco{}.

> Tabasco is the secret ingredient for that perfect Cajun kick - add as little or as much as you like depending on how much you want to spice things up.

Add in the @basmati rice{1} and the @chopped tomatoes{1%tin} together with @chicken stock{300%ml}. On medium-low heat cook with a #lid{} on for ~{10%minutes}. Remove the lid for the final ~{10%minutes}.

After 20 mins taste a bit of rice to see if it is cooked and seasoned enough. Adjust @salt{} and @pepper{} as necessary and add a little more water if you need too.

> A proper Jambalaya is nice and saucy when cooked.

Once the rice is perfectly cooked stir in all but a sprinkle of finely chopped parsley. For a finishing flourish sprinkle over a little more parsley and squeeze over a bit more orange juice.